3 3. Establish or enforce any standard, rule, or policy that
4 precludes consideration of a current or prospective adoptive or
5 foster parent for any particular placement based, in whole or in
6 part, upon the parent’s sincerely held religious or moral beliefs
7 regarding sexual orientation or gender identity.
8 B. Nothing in this section shall:
9 1. Preclude the Department from taking into account the
10 religious or moral beliefs of a particular adoptive or foster child,
11 or his or her family of origin including, but not limited to, the
12 child’s or family’s views regarding sexual orientation and gender
13 identity, considered in relation to the religious or moral beliefs
14 of a prospective adoptive or foster parent when determining which
15 placement is in the best interest of the child; or
16 2. Be construed to prohibit or relieve the Department of its
17 duty to make each placement consistent with the best interests of
18 the child as otherwise required by law.
19 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
